  "texts": [
    "As a result, scene classification would solve the dilemma of huge intra-class variability and minimal inter-class variety.",
    "Feature extraction is an important stage in image classification, and much of the present research focuses on defining image features more accurately.",
    "Traditional classification approaches rely on mid-level or low-level features [13]; however, these features are difficult to adequately describe the semantic content of remote sensing scenes, resulting in disappointing results.",
    "As a result, subsequent studies have concentrated on developing more complex approaches for automatically learning the high-level image features representations.Deep learning has been developed in many computer vision applications, including object detection, segmentation, and scene recognition [14].Researchers use the CNN networks in RS image classification to extract high-level semantic features.",
    "Most of them depend on the pre-trained CNN models for feature extraction in remote sensing images, such as VGGNet, CaffeNet [15], and GoogleNet [16]."
